    • Method Detail

      • fromFile

        static NucleotideFastaFileDataStore fromFile(File fastaFile)
                                      throws IOException
        Create a NucleotideFastaDataStore of all the records in the given fasta file. Warning! This usually stores all the records in memory use fromFile(File, DataStoreProviderHint) or NucleotideFastaFileDataStoreBuilder to handle the file or datastore implementation differently.
        API Note:
        As of Jillion 5.1, this will also look for a FastaIndex (.fai) file using the standard naming conventions and is equivalent to 
         new NucleotideFastaFileDataStoreBuilder(fastaFile, new File(fastaFile.getParentFile(), fastaFile.getName() + ".fai"));
        Parameters:
        fastaFile - the fasta file make a NucleotideFastaDataStore with; can not be null and must exist.
        Returns:
        a new NucleotideFastaDataStore; will never be null.
        Throws:
        IOException - if the fasta file does not exist, or can not be read.
        NullPointerException - if fastaFile is null.
        Since:
        5.3
        See Also:
        NucleotideFastaFileDataStoreBuilder, fromFile(File, DataStoreProviderHint)

      • fromFile

        static NucleotideFastaFileDataStore fromFile(File fastaFile,
                                             DataStoreProviderHint hint)
                                      throws IOException
        Create a NucleotideFastaDataStore of all the records in the given fasta file with the given DataStoreProviderHint to help jillion choose a datastore implementation. If filtering records is desired, pleas use NucleotideFastaFileDataStoreBuilder.
        API Note:
        As of Jillion 5.1, this will also look for a FastaIndex (.fai) file using the standard naming conventions and is equivalent to 
         new NucleotideFastaFileDataStoreBuilder(fastaFile, new File(fastaFile.getParentFile(), fastaFile.getName() + ".fai"));
        Parameters:
        fastaFile - the fasta file make a NucleotideFastaDataStore with; can not be null and must exist.
        hint - the DataStoreProviderHint to use; can not be null.
        Returns:
        a new NucleotideFastaDataStore; will never be null.
        Throws:
        IOException - if the fasta file does not exist, or can not be read.
        NullPointerException - if any parameter is null.
        Since:
        5.3
        See Also:
        NucleotideFastaFileDataStoreBuilder

      • getFile

        Optional<File> getFile()
        Get the actual File that this datastore wraps. Note, because of datastore filtering and other decorators, the file may contain additional reads not present in this datastore and the NucleotideFastaRecords that are present, may not match 100% to the input file. It is also possible that this file uses some kind of compression that this datastore knows how to decompress.
        Returns:
        an Optional File, if it is known.
        Since:
        5.3
